@reine12

Funny how you throw around the word irony(incorrectly i might add). You attack someone for stating their opinion on a movie, then argue with another commenter that users have a right to their own opinions? Hypocritical, much?

His post was useful in the fact that he rated the quality of the torrent and then offered his opinion. You offered nothing but insults... no matter how many smiley icons you put in your insult, it's still an insult. Yes, opinions are opinions, but when the majority of opinions tend to agree with one another, they become statistical... and useful.
